Find the greatest common divisor of 91 and 72.
inference:
Prime factorizations:
$$91=7\cdot13$$
$$72=2^3\cdot3^2$$
The greatest common divisor is the product of the common prime factors, each raised to the lowest power that it appears in any of the factorizations. 
The only common prime factor is 7, and it appears to the first power in both factorizations.
So the greatest common divisor is $$7^1=\boxed{7}$$
Final Answer: \boxed{$7$}. I hope it is correct.
